default5.default              defaultConclusionsdefault&#xa0;default5.1
default              
defaultThe CEA does not believe there is sufficient evidence to justify the need 
defaultfor deregulation of premises l
defaulticenses for community premises.
default&#xa0;
default5.2
default              
defaultOption 2 potentially creates a series of loopholes.  It fosters a lack of proper oversight and assurance of safety and child protection which audiences of all types have come to expect and 
defaultdemand.
default&#xa0;
default5.3
default              
defaultNew costs and burdens on the licensing regime for venues exhibiting films could adversely affect the time spent by licensing authorities on managing queries and categorising venues.  In the view of the CEA and its members, large and small, 
defaultthis risks public safety, especially if there is no means of tracking venues who consider themselves community premises.
default&#xa0;
default5.4
default              
defaultLack of clarity over
default the
default definition of community venue status in particular opens loopholes which give implicit encouragement to p
defaultrofit-making venues to flout copyright and content controls.
default 
default&#xa0;
default5.5
default              
defaultWe do not oppose proportionate, thoughtful and well-defined deregulation to enable community film exhibition to flourish.  However, 
defaultfor
default the reasons stated in this response, we strongly beli
defaulteve that the 
defaultproposal 
defaultput forward 
defaultdoes not meet these criteria.
